00:56:21,975 --> 00:56:23,442
Of course.

837
00:56:23,510 --> 00:56:28,277
You get on top
of this shit pile...

838
00:56:28,348 --> 00:56:30,816
and then the job's
not such a ballbuster.

839
00:56:30,884 --> 00:56:33,284
You'll be happier then.

840
00:56:33,353 --> 00:56:34,843
I'm not complaining.

841
00:56:34,921 --> 00:56:36,684
Are you unhappy?

842
00:56:36,756 --> 00:56:39,691
It sure sounds like it to me.

843
00:56:50,237 --> 00:56:52,933
I'm not in this business for my health.

844
00:56:53,006 --> 00:56:54,940
Or anybody else's.

845
00:56:55,008 --> 00:56:56,737
I'm doing my inventory.

846
00:56:56,810 --> 00:56:59,677
It's a pain in the ass.

847
00:56:59,746 --> 00:57:03,409
Ain't been anybody from Wakefield
helping me lately.

848
00:57:03,483 --> 00:57:06,611
We're not sending
convicts to you anymore.

849
00:57:06,686 --> 00:57:08,916
That's slave labor.

850
00:57:08,989 --> 00:57:10,889
It is not.

851
00:57:10,957 --> 00:57:13,187
You got it all backwards...

852
00:57:13,260 --> 00:57:15,387
because this is a community.

853
00:57:15,462 --> 00:57:17,453
The people around here...

854
00:57:17,530 --> 00:57:19,395
don't ostracize this prison.

855
00:57:19,466 --> 00:57:21,093
We accept it.

856
00:57:21,167 --> 00:57:22,395
We cooperate.

857
00:57:22,469 --> 00:57:24,937
It's a two-way street.

858
00:57:25,005 --> 00:57:28,406
You'll see a lot of nice things...

859
00:57:28,475 --> 00:57:32,741
from people in
the farm supply business...

860
00:57:32,812 --> 00:57:34,109
clothing business...

861
00:57:34,180 --> 00:57:35,579
Lumber business.

862
00:57:35,649 --> 00:57:37,412
Yeah. Take that cake.

863
00:57:37,484 --> 00:57:41,284
The point ain't whether
you like prune.

864
00:57:41,354 --> 00:57:43,481
It's the thought that counts.

865
00:57:43,556 --> 00:57:45,319
Exactly.

866
00:57:45,392 --> 00:57:48,987
Just accept the stuff,
keep your mouth shut...

867
00:57:49,062 --> 00:57:51,189
and let things run...

868
00:57:51,264 --> 00:57:54,597
like they've been
going for 100 years...

869
00:57:54,668 --> 00:57:56,431
before we was born.

870
00:57:56,503 --> 00:57:58,903
I'm talking about tradition.

871
00:57:58,972 --> 00:58:00,963
Don't fuck with tradition.

872
00:58:01,041 --> 00:58:03,305
Count your own woodpile, Woody.

873
00:58:03,376 --> 00:58:05,640
I'll fix my own roof.

874
00:58:05,712 --> 00:58:09,580
A lot of people will be
disappointed in you.

875
00:58:09,649 --> 00:58:12,447
It won't be the first time.

876
00:58:12,519 --> 00:58:14,077
I hope you're right.

877
00:58:14,154 --> 00:58:15,712
Take this.

878
00:58:15,789 --> 00:58:20,453
Get me all the contracts on that roof.

879
00:58:20,527 --> 00:58:22,586
I want everything.

880
00:58:22,662 --> 00:58:24,755
Whose team you on?

881
00:58:24,831 --> 00:58:26,765
What can I say?

882
00:58:26,833 --> 00:58:28,767
He's the coach.

883
00:58:28,835 --> 00:58:30,462
Short season.

884
00:58:38,211 --> 00:58:41,305
Oh, no, it's no secret.

885
00:58:41,381 --> 00:58:43,815
They write it all down.

886
00:58:43,883 --> 00:58:45,817
Prison lumber and labor...

887
00:58:45,885 --> 00:58:48,820
is building people's swimming pools.

888
00:58:48,888 --> 00:58:50,185
That's right.

889
00:58:50,256 --> 00:58:55,125
My trusty is loading our food
into state police cars.

890
00:58:55,195 --> 00:58:56,924
It runs that deep?

891
00:58:56,996 --> 00:59:00,659
We're stepping on more toes
than I imagined.

892
00:59:02,402 --> 00:59:04,336
What's that?

893
00:59:06,806 --> 00:59:08,774
I'm just warning you...

894
00:59:08,842 --> 00:59:11,936
because you're likely
to start hearing things.

895
00:59:12,011 --> 00:59:16,277
I'll be ready to run
interference for you.

896
00:59:16,349 --> 00:59:18,783
I'll talk to the governor.

897
00:59:18,852 --> 00:59:22,447
Can I call you back?

898
00:59:22,522 --> 00:59:23,784
Uh-huh.

899
00:59:23,857 --> 00:59:25,415
Bye.

900
00:59:25,492 --> 00:59:27,016
[Dial Tone]

901
00:59:43,143 --> 00:59:45,976
Give me some of that stuff.

902
01:00:41,201 --> 01:00:43,897
Where, uh, where's Huey Rauch?

903
01:00:43,970 --> 01:00:45,562
I don't see him around.

904
01:01:16,169 --> 01:01:18,262
Smell this.

905
01:01:22,141 --> 01:01:23,870
I'm a city boy.

906
01:01:23,943 --> 01:01:25,069
Purcell?

907
01:01:32,385 --> 01:01:34,785
That smells like kerosene.

908
01:02:14,861 --> 01:02:17,091
This animal's been shot.

909
01:02:17,163 --> 01:02:19,825
You know anything about it?

910
01:02:21,668 --> 01:02:24,694
What about that truck out there?

911
01:02:24,771 --> 01:02:26,796
Looked like a free worlder.

912
01:02:49,629 --> 01:02:51,620
Now what are these?

913
01:02:51,698 --> 01:02:54,258
I don't know.

914
01:02:57,270 --> 01:02:58,931
Shacks.

915
01:02:59,005 --> 01:03:01,473
Are they on our property?

916
01:03:01,541 --> 01:03:03,475
Let me think.

917
01:03:06,179 --> 01:03:08,909
Honestly...

918
01:03:08,982 --> 01:03:10,381
Yeah!

919
01:03:10,450 --> 01:03:12,111
I think.

920
01:03:12,185 --> 01:03:13,709
Shit.

921
01:03:18,891 --> 01:03:23,157
I don't know who's in there
or what you're up to...

922
01:03:23,229 --> 01:03:26,790
but we got the new warden,
and we're probably coming in!

923
01:03:26,866 --> 01:03:29,061
Right?

924
01:03:31,004 --> 01:03:33,131
[Voices]

925
01:03:33,206 --> 01:03:35,697
Probably nobody home.

926
01:03:35,775 --> 01:03:38,403
I ain't hiding in the dark...

927
01:03:38,478 --> 01:03:41,038
like no human insect.

928
01:03:44,984 --> 01:03:46,747
Yeah? What?

929
01:03:46,819 --> 01:03:49,344
Good morning.

930
01:03:49,422 --> 01:03:50,411
Morning.

931
01:03:50,490 --> 01:03:54,586
Get out here
and take care of this.

932
01:03:54,661 --> 01:03:57,892
Excuse me, I have
a tight schedule.

933
01:03:57,964 --> 01:04:01,661
[Television]... like some animal
with one thing on his mind.

934
01:04:01,734 --> 01:04:05,602
Oh, Mother,
even kids can have sex.

935
01:04:05,672 --> 01:04:08,106
Is that what
you do at parties?

936
01:04:08,174 --> 01:04:10,506
How many out there?

937
01:04:10,576 --> 01:04:12,066
Three, four.

938
01:04:12,145 --> 01:04:15,080
I don't want you
getting a reputation.

939
01:04:15,148 --> 01:04:16,809
Pull it up.

940
01:04:16,883 --> 01:04:20,944
I already have one.
The wrong kind.

941
01:04:21,020 --> 01:04:24,148
Marry a man
who respects you.

942
01:04:24,223 --> 01:04:28,182
I want you to have
a good name.

943
01:04:28,261 --> 01:04:30,821
You.! You want.!

944
01:04:30,897 --> 01:04:33,798
Is that all
you can say?

945
01:04:33,866 --> 01:04:38,064
Uh... you want a beer
or something?

946
01:04:38,137 --> 01:04:40,833
Don't talk
like that again.!

947
